Vice President Mike Pence gave a speech at the Loews Atlanta Hotel in Atlanta, Georgia, where he discussed the progress made by the Trump administration over the past year. He thanked the people of Georgia for their support and highlighted accomplishments such as historic tax cuts, increased defense spending, and efforts to combat the opioid crisis. Pence also emphasized the importance of rebuilding America's infrastructure and fixing the broken immigration system. He called on the audience to spread the message of the administration's achievements and to pray for the country. Pence expressed confidence that with continued support and leadership, America would become safe, prosperous, and great again.